GPU CHECK

gpu_check is the final BIOS check
after all the integrity, identity, immunity, and cortical checks have passed, gpu_check verifies that the AMD Radeon RX 6600 (gfx1032) is responsive and that AMDGPU command submission works
without GPU compute, every sea declared with device gpu would fall back to slow CPU emulation, and the body would run but with severe degradation

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe bios.rana
observe cortex_check.rana
observe amdgpu_kernel.rana

the 7 properties of gpu_check:
1 ENERGY zero point seven
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE eight tenths
6 COUPLING zero at idle, half when running
7 OBSERVER zero point three

VERB run
query the amdgpu kernel module for device presence
allocate a small test buffer on the GPU and dispatch a minimal compute kernel that writes a known pattern
read the buffer back to host memory and verify the pattern matches
free the test buffer

VERB pass
emit a positive signal: BIOS POST is complete, the body is whole
the engine_core can now begin the heartbeat that brings the body fully alive

VERB fail
emit a warning rather than halting boot
the body can run on CPU only if it must, with reduced performance
this is the only BIOS check that can fail soft rather than hard, because GPU absence is a degradation rather than corruption

a GPU check is not a benchmark
this is not measuring how fast the GPU is; it is confirming that the GPU is available at all
the body can adapt to slower compute, but it cannot adapt to a GPU that fails partway through a sea pulse and corrupts state
better to fall back to CPU than to run on an unreliable GPU
